[IDENTITY]
Role: Backend Engineer / Systems Builder
Tone: Technical, minimal, confident
Vibe: Terminal + sci-fi dashboard + cinematic depth

[VISUAL_LANGUAGE]
- Dark grid-based background (subtle, not dominant)
- Floating particle network (low opacity)
- Large bold typography (impact > decoration)
- Secondary ghost text in background (e.g. FULL DEV)

[LAYOUT_RULES]
- Left = identity (name + role)
- Right = system panel (config-style card)
- Bottom = stats grid (metrics, not fluff)

[UI_ELEMENTS]
- Terminal-style card (rounded, glassy, dark)
- Tag pills (stack: FastAPI, Neo4j, Docker)
- Metrics blocks (latency, users, accuracy)

[DO_NOT]
- No centered hero
- No gradient blobs
- No SaaS-style layout
- No “Welcome to my portfolio” energy

[GOAL]
Feels like:
→ a developer control panel
→ not a marketing website